The paper deals with the problem of computing the k-visibility region of a point in a polygon, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the memory-constrained model, which is a common topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The time-space trade-off algorithm presented in the paper involves probabilistic analysis, which is a common technique in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also deals with the problem of computing the visibility region for polygons with holes and sets of non-crossing line segments, which falls under the scope of cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
